  "prompt": "How do you remember words?",
  "response": "There are several strategies to help remember words:\n\n1. Repetition and practice\n- Writing the word multiple times\n- Saying the word out loud\n- Using flashcards\n- Repeating words in context\n\n2. Mnemonic techniques\n- Creating memorable associations\n- Using acronyms\n- Making mental images or stories\n- Connecting new words to words you already know\n\n3. Visual learning\n- Linking words to pictures\n- Writing words with visual cues\n- Using color coding\n\n4. Contextual learning\n- Reading words in sentences\n- Using words in conversation\n- Listening to words in context\n\n5. Sensory engagement\n- Writing words\n- Speaking words\n- Listening to words\n- Using gestures or movements\n\n6. Systematic approaches\n- Breaking words into syllables\n- Learning word roots and etymology\n- Understanding word patterns\n- Grouping similar words\n\n7. Technology tools\n- Language learning apps\n- Spaced repetition software\n- Audio and video resources\n\n8. Active recall\n- Testing yourself\n- Using the words in different contexts\n- Challenging yourself to recall words without looking\n\nThe most effective method varies by individual learning style.",
